<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870515-0008 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Pacific Lighting Corp.</HL><DD> 05/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PLT </IN><TEXT>   PACIFIC LIGHTING CORP. shareholders approved an increase in the diversified utility's authorized shares to 300 million from 130 million. The Los Angeles-based company said it wants the new shares for future financing, acquisitions and other corporate purposes. Paul A. Miller, chairman, said the company has no plans to issue the stock. Pacific Lighting had 59 million shares outstanding as of March 20. </TEXT></DOC>